Nick Muir - G Platz 2007 [ST] [Progressive House]


[ST] = Selected Tracks


As played on John Digweed&amp;#039;s BBC Radio 1 Essential Mix.


&quot; Nick Muir is best known as one half of the legendary production team, Bedrock, who have given us some of dance music&amp;#039;s enduring classics such as &amp;#039;For What You Dream Of&amp;#039; and &amp;#039;Heaven Scent&amp;#039;. &amp;#039;G Platz is possibly his finest solo outing to date and comes with remixes from Pig &amp; Dan along with Bedrock resident Neil Quigley. &quot;



There is no discogs entry for this release as yet.


Label: Audio Therapy
Catalogue Number: AT041


Released : November 5th 2007


Nick Muir - G Platz (Original Mix) [9:29]

Nick Muir - G Platz (Pig &amp; Dan Remix) [7:34]


39.0MB

320KBps Digital Release.



The entire release comprises of 4 tracks, but we are only concerned with the 2 contained here.

The reviews are not wrong.  This is Nick Muir&amp;#039;s finest moment in production to date and possibly the best release all year on the Audio Therapy label.


For those who may be unaware, Pig &amp; Dan is a name in the fields of Progressive, Tech and Minimal, spoken with utmost respect... and they really have outdone themselves with this superb remix which I just can&amp;#039;t seem to keep away from for too long.


